<asp:Content ID="BodyContent" runat="server" ContentPlaceHolderID="MainContent">
    <h1>
        About
    </h1>
    <p>
        CricketOnline.info has been designed to be used throughout the world as a resource for all clubs playing the game in any form of competitve structure.<br /><br />
        The site allows for leagues, clubs, teams, & individual to record as many or as few statistics and results as they wish and then present this information for common good.<br />
        
        <h2>League Administration</h2><br />
        As a League Administrator you may define the structure of your league, the rules, divisional structure, clubs, teams and importatntly fixtures so that all may view and contribute.<br /><br />
        You, as a League administator retain the rights to moderate input from Club officials or Players and ensure that all details are correctly displayed. However you also have the right to delegate these responsibilities to other trusted individuals.
    
    <h2>Club Administration</h2><br />
    As a Club Administrator you have the permissions to manage your teams & players, submit results and other information to the site and communicate with the club in general.<br /><br />
    Club statistics, records, averages, ground information and history may also be updated and maintained.<br /><br />
    <h2>Players</h2><br />
    Players have the ability to update information about themselves, view statistics and averages, check fictures, league tables, histories and Club/League notices</p>
</asp:Content>
